    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Supporting elements in the shape of human figures. For piers with engaged figures where the pier, not the statue, supports the entablature, see, for example, "Osiride pillars."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000094828/Getty Vocabulary Program rules</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Voor pijlers met verzonken figuurvoorstellingen, waarbij de pijler (en niet het standbeeld) de entablementen ondersteunt, zie, bijvoorbeeld, 'Osiris-zuilen'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052401/Vandenberghe, Elseviers Dictionary of Architecture (1988)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以含人物形象的墩柱（非神像）支撐柱頂楣構，如「歐斯利得柱」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Elementos de suporte em forma de figuras humanas. Para pilares com figuras engajadas onde o pilar, e não a estátua, sustenta o entablamento, consulte, por exemplo, "Pilares de Osiride".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
